Package org.bluezoo.gumdrop.mailbox

Class MessageSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bluezoo.gumdrop.mailbox.MessageSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<MessageSet.Range>
    public final class MessageSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<MessageSet.Range>
    Represents an IMAP message set (sequence set or UID set).

    A message set specifies a collection of message numbers or UIDs. It can contain single numbers, ranges, and wildcards. Examples:

    • 5 - single message 5
    • 1:10 - messages 1 through 10
    • * - the last message (wildcard)
    • 10:* - messages 10 through the last
    • 1:5,7,10:* - combination of ranges

    The same structure is used for both sequence numbers (message order) and UIDs (unique identifiers). The interpretation depends on context.

    Author:
    Chris Burdess
    See Also:
    RFC 9051 Section 4.1.1
